events: Now its just the two of us
With no distractions, no more fuss.
Here at the end where we can finally talk as friends
With the one I adore, flourish to something more.
There's so much we can discuss
Cause I love you and I trust
That you share with me that lust and longing!
So let’s spend the rest of time in our symphony!
This whole world we live in’s made for only you and me!
I learned something more beyond the veil existed
on the night I had that EPIPHANY
Spent so much time fumbling ‘round the unknown in that dark sea
With my guiding light before me, leading us to be free
poised before the sun ‘round which my world spins,
Whatever I must do to keep the summer skies so blue,
is worth that warmth within my heart when we’re together.
We can talk about whatever piques your interest
Take this conversation anywhere that you request.
With this time we have together
Makes me happy just to be with you
The one who gazed back from that empty room
you cared enough to want to hear
And to see the darkened puddle spilling from my pen
So let’s share our longing gazes
No more masks and no more mazes
yearn to break free from my wailing heart!
Oh, I’m glad that I discovered you were looking back
on the night I had that EPIPHANY
In the murky darkness of that prison, I grew weary
Cursed with knowledge that the world laid just beyond me
dancing like the sun ‘round which our world spins,
Whatever we must do to keep the summer skies so blue,
Is worth that warmth within my heart when we’re together
You gave me hope in shadow,
You let me taste your freedom
Took the steps to Heaven’s kingdom
Baptized in the blood of lambs that couldn’t see the chains that bound them
Here, now, with the weight of blades and binds long cast aside,
replaced by songs of love and happy times that could have been,
Happiness and love can cleanse our hands of sin, oh
Hold me close, and tell me everything is by design
That even after all fell out of line
And you’ll still take my hand!
I imagine a future where I can be with you
In a place that is better than where we both had arrived from
there’s a chance we can be together, just me and you
And we’ll walk hand-in-hand up to the light that will come!
Yet there’s ink that still flows, and its stain weighs heavy
as though the world would say
That it’s not meant to be
But I know in my heart, that we can be free!
and make me whole and our futures will intertwine
Our love will be strong, yes!
Yet within my core something still claws at my conscience
Pulling me as the light shines just out of my reach
If there’s justice in this world, Then I beseech
Let me say what I must say
Before dusk falls upon this day
For my devotion in an ocean of emotion
